No choice for zero stars? I begin noting that my wife is from Ireland where our son was born. While attempting to come in on holidays at 4pm or so on Wednesday with our children, the female dosser behind the bar shouted that "they weren't allowed in here". When my wife politely asked why, she was told because they aren't 21. Pubs in Ireland allow children, simple as. They do expect they be out by 9pm. While every establishment is entitled to their own rules about service, the female dosser behind the bar's attitude was out of order and lousy. This review is written for the particular benefit of Irish people, but also anyone else who may be travelling great length to New Orleans. Spend your money elsewhere and avoid a mouthy little dosser peddling fake Irish pub kitsch.

Went in the next night and meet Saorise, who was equally nice and welcoming (and gave us tips for when we visit County Kerry, Ireland, as she's from there).  Good drinks, fair prices, nice people.
